{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0184em3XSNHxPcSLoYhj41E4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very interesting! The replica set commands require authentication. This means that the admin user has already been created (which ends the localhost exception). But rs.status() from the `kubectl exec` is running `mongosh` without credentials and it's getting an auth error.\n\nWait, but if auth is required, that means users exist... but if users exist, that means the initialization completed successfully at some point! Let me check if the marker file exists.\n\nActually, wait. \"Command replSetInitiate requires authentication\" means auth is required. If there are no users yet, the localhost exception would bypass auth. So if auth is REQUIRED, it means:\n1. Either a user has been created already (initialization succeeded!)\n2. Or something else is going on\n\nLet me check if the marker file exists and whether the replica set was initialized.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":655,"cache_read_input_tokens":77846,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":655},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"443b4199-f7ba-4509-b361-5d3d6fdcb4c6","uuid":"b355b626-472e-47d7-bd2b-2fa66c7ef916","request_id":"req_011CcPnZeeM3t73DScEv4NCp"}
